[{'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'role': 'Advisory Committee', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'Vegan Trade Council', 'logo': None, 'url': None}, 'cause': None, 'description': 'http://www.vegantradecouncil.com/

The mission of the Vegan Trade Council is:

to promote vegan products in the marketplace 

to provide a central voice for the vegan industry to the press and to the public

to develop a go-to online resource for information of interest to the general public on vegan products, as well as the issues important to the industry

to conduct legislative and regulatory activities in order to provide a fair environment in which vegan products can be produced and sold

to sponsor research to benefit the vegan industry

The animal-based product industries all have trade associations to advance their interests and to advocate for their products in the press, in legislative and regulatory affairs, and in the marketplace. These trade associations have been and continue to be effective, because they represent the views and dollars of their entire respective industries. 

While there are a number of animal welfare groups that do engage in the activities cited above, the vegan product industry, as an industry, has had no trade association to date to rival the trade associations working on behalf of the animal-based industries. 

The Vegan Trade Council will represent the vegan industry needs in the same vein as the animal-based industries.
